# Aggregate Persistence

`<AggregateName>`  is the placeholder in this document of the aggregate name you are going to implement.

## Aggregate Conventions

- Aggregates must be persisted trough a repository implementing an interface that provides these methods:
  - `persist(<AggregateClassName> $<AggregateName>): void;`
  - `restore(<AggregateIdClassName> $<AggregateName>Id): ?<AggregateClassName>;`
  - `remove(<AggregateIdClassName> $<AggregateName>Id): void`
  - `generateId(): <AggregateName>Id` — MUST always return a new aggregate ID and MUST NOT return `null` (nullable return types for this method were incorrect).
  - Implementations typically delegate to `UuidGeneratorInterface` (or equivalent) and wrap the result in the ID value object; use cases MUST NOT null-check `generateId()`.
  - This interface MUST NOT have additional methods.
- The repository MUST be placed in `src/Capability/<CapabilityName>/Domain/Repositories/<AggregateName>WriteRepositoryInterface.php`
- An aggregate SHOULD implement `\JsonSerializable` (see https://www.php.net/manual/en/class.jsonserializable.php) and recursivly serialze the whole object to JSON
- Tests for the aggregate MUST be placed in `tests/Capability/<CapabilityName>/Domain/Model/<AggregateName>`

## Aggregate Respository Implementation

- The repository implementation MUST be placed in `src/Capability/<CapabilityName>/Infrastructure/Persistence/<PersistenceType>/<AggregateName>WriteRepository.php`.
- The write repository orchestrates **transactions**, **query execution**, **mapper calls**, and **domain event publishing** only. It MUST NOT contain aggregate mapping logic (no `new Aggregate(...)`, no hand-built row arrays from aggregate fields, no `ObjectAccessor` usage in the repository class).
- Aggregate **construction and deconstruction** (object ↔ array for persistence) MUST live in `<AggregateName>Mapper.php` under `Mapper/`, using `App\Shared\Infrastructure\ObjectAccessor\ObjectAccessorFactoryInterface` and `App\Shared\Infrastructure\ObjectAccessor\ObjectAccessorInterface`. Treat deep graphs recursively as needed.
- That mapper is **only** for the write/restore path of the domain aggregate. Do **not** use it for Application read models; read-side mapping is defined in `read-models.mdc` (constructor-based mappers, separate classes).
- Persisting the data of the whole aggregate MUST be wrapped into a transction to ensure the whole aggregate is saved.
- When an aggregate is deleted all of its related data MUST be deleted unless specified otherwise.
- The repository MUST use `App\Shared\Infrastructure\Persistence\QueryBuilder\QueryBuilderFactoryInterface` to create query builders.
- All database operations (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) MUST be performed using query builders, not directly through the connection.
- The repository MUST have a private method `createQueryBuilder()` that uses the query builder factory to create the appropriate query builder instance.

### Aggregate mapper (write path)

- Naming: `<AggregateName>Mapper` next to the write repository (e.g. `fromArrayToObject`, `fromObjectToArray` or project-equivalent).
- Implements all ObjectAccessor-driven mapping for that aggregate; the write repository only passes rows or aggregates to this mapper.

## Examples

### Repository Example

```php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Capability\Badges\Infrastructure\Persistence\Doctrine;

use App\Capability\Badges\Domain\Model\Badge\Badge;
use App\Capability\Badges\Domain\Model\Badge\BadgeId;
use App\Capability\Badges\Domain\Repositories\BadgeWriteRepositoryInterface;
use App\Capability\Badges\Infrastructure\Persistence\Doctrine\Mapper\BadgeMapper;
use App\Capability\Badges\Infrastructure\Persistence\Doctrine\QueryBuilder\BadgeQueryBuilder;
use App\Shared\Application\UuidGenerator\UuidGeneratorInterface;
use App\Shared\Infrastructure\EventBus\DomainEventPublisherInterface;
use App\Shared\Infrastructure\Persistence\QueryBuilder\QueryBuilderFactoryInterface;
use Doctrine\DBAL\Connection;

readonly class BadgeWriteRepository implements BadgeWriteRepositoryInterface
{
    private const string TABLE_NAME = 'badge';

    public function __construct(
        private Connection $connection,
        private BadgeMapper $badgeMapper,
        private DomainEventPublisherInterface $domainEventPublisher,
        private UuidGeneratorInterface $uuidGenerator,
        private QueryBuilderFactoryInterface $queryBuilderFactory
    ) {
    }

    public function persist(Badge $badge): void
    {
        $data = $this->badgeMapper->fromObjectToArray($badge);

        $this->connection->transactional(function () use ($badge, $data): void {
            $exists = $this->findCount((string)$badge->getBadgeId()) > 0;

            if (!$exists) {
                $this->createQueryBuilder()
                    ->insert(self::TABLE_NAME)
                    ->values($data)
                    ->executeStatement();
                return;
            }

            $this->createQueryBuilder()
                ->update(self::TABLE_NAME)
                ->setValues($data)
                ->andWhere('id = :id')
                ->setParameter('id', (string)$badge->getBadgeId())
                ->executeStatement();
        });

        $this->domainEventPublisher->publishFromAggregate($badge);
    }

    public function restore(BadgeId $badgeId): ?Badge
    {
        $data = $this->createQueryBuilder()
            ->select('*')
            ->from(self::TABLE_NAME)
            ->where('id = :id')
            ->setParameter('id', (string)$badgeId)
            ->fetchAssociative();

        if (!$data) {
            return null;
        }

        return $this->badgeMapper->fromArrayToObject($data);
    }

    public function remove(Badge $badge): void
    {
        $badgeId = $badge->getBadgeId();
        $badge->delete();

        $this->connection->transactional(function () use ($badgeId): void {
            $this->createQueryBuilder()
                ->delete('badge_assignment')
                ->where('badge_id = :badgeId')
                ->setParameter('badgeId', (string)$badgeId)
                ->executeStatement();

            $this->createQueryBuilder()
                ->delete(self::TABLE_NAME)
                ->where('id = :id')
                ->setParameter('id', (string)$badgeId)
                ->executeStatement();
        });

        $this->domainEventPublisher->publishFromAggregate($badge);
    }

    public function generateId(): BadgeId
    {
        return BadgeId::fromString($this->uuidGenerator->generateV7());
    }

    private function findCount(string $badgeId): int
    {
        $result = $this->createQueryBuilder()
            ->select('COUNT(*) as count')
            ->from(self::TABLE_NAME)
            ->where('id = :id')
            ->setParameter('id', $badgeId)
            ->fetchAssociative();

        return $result ? (int)$result['count'] : 0;
    }

    private function createQueryBuilder(): BadgeQueryBuilder
    {
        $queryBuilder = $this->queryBuilderFactory->fromClassName(BadgeQueryBuilder::class);
        assert($queryBuilder instanceof BadgeQueryBuilder);

        return $queryBuilder;
    }
}
```
